phase-1 / QA & Testing Agent (re-record)

This run re-audits the phase-1 QA deliverables that landed in commit
`e2484bf` ("phase-1(qa): tiered test harness, unit + integration + rls
suites") and were re-recorded in `7bdb5ed`. The harness is wired, the
unit gate is green, and the env-gated integration / RLS suites self-
skip cleanly without TEST_SUPABASE_* configured. The re-pins under
Next 15 + ESLint 9 + async `cookies()` (3a6e048) and the Database /
Auth / Core API / Frontend agent re-records (b064799, f81d221, 22e6d7c,
4323569, 7bdb5ed, 66ea7cb, 032cdde, 04d38a8, 767cf52) have not moved
any contract this suite depends on; lint, type-check, and unit gates
all stay green. No code changes were necessary. Artifact: this log.

## WHAT I DID

- **Re-audited every file in the QA & Testing agent's owned area for
  Phase 1** (`/tests/**` plus `vitest.config.ts` and the CI workflow):

  - `vitest.config.ts` - Vitest 2.1.9, node environment, single config
    driving three opt-in scopes via `--dir`. Aliases for `@/app`,
    `@/components`, `@/lib`, `@/tests`, plus a `server-only` -> empty-
    stub alias so route-handler imports don't blow up under Node. 20s
    test / 30s hook timeouts accommodate Supabase latency without
    letting hung integration tests stall CI.
  - `tests/_helpers/env.ts` - `readTestSupabaseEnv()`, `noTestSupabaseEnv()`,
    `requireTestSupabaseEnv()`. TEST_SUPABASE_* contract is deliberately
    independent of the app's NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_* so a misconfigured
    shell can never aim the suite at a teammate's dev project.
  - `tests/_helpers/supabase-clients.ts` - `adminClient` (service role,
    bypasses RLS for fixture setup), `anonClient` (anonymous, verifies
    blocked reads), `asUserClient(accessToken)` (carries a user JWT so
    PostgREST evaluates RLS against `auth.uid()`).
  - `tests/_helpers/test-users.ts` - `createTestUser`, `deleteTestUsers`,
    `createCompanionProfile`. Mints auth.users + the public.users mirror
    via admin, signs in via the password grant to obtain a real
    access_token, returns an authenticated client. Per-test unique
    emails (ts + counter + pid) keep concurrent suites safe.
  - `tests/_helpers/server-only-stub.ts` - empty module aliased over the
    `server-only` marker so files like
    `app/api/profiles/_lib/auth.ts` can be imported under Vitest.

- **Re-verified the three layers each cover exactly what the phase-1
  task list calls for** (unit, integration, RLS):

  Unit (`tests/unit/`, 5 files, 50/50 passing - the CI merge gate):
    - `auth-gate.test.ts` - 9 tests. `requireAuth` branches: 401 (no
      session), 401 (getUser error), 500 (mirror lookup error), 403
      (auth row exists but no mirror), 200 (happy path).
      `requireCompanionMode` branches: 409 (`companion_mode_required`),
      200 (is_companion), 401 propagation, 403 propagation. Mocks
      `@/app/api/profiles/_lib/db#profilesServerClient` and
      `next/headers` via `vi.hoisted` shared state so a regression in
      authorization shows up without a live DB.
    - `parse-json-body.test.ts` - 3 tests. `parseJsonBody` is the only
      entry point through which caller JSON reaches the profiles API,
      so its failure modes are part of the authorization story
      (server-side input validation). Pins ok-path, malformed-JSON ->
      400 invalid_input (no `details`), ZodError -> 400 invalid_input
      (with `details = ZodError.flatten()`).
    - `api-errors.test.ts` - 8 tests. Pins the
      `code -> HTTP status` table on the frozen error envelope
      (`unauthenticated`/401, `forbidden`/403, `not_found`/404,
      `invalid_input`/400, `conflict`/409, `companion_mode_required`/409,
      `internal_error`/500), and that `details` is omitted unless
      supplied.
    - `enums-transitions.test.ts` - 11 tests. Pins
      `REQUEST_NEXT_STATES` (only `requested` has outgoing edges; the
      other four states are terminal) and `BOOKING_NEXT_STATES`
      (`accepted -> confirmed | cancelled`,
      `confirmed -> completed | cancelled`; both `completed` and
      `cancelled` terminal). Explicit guards: NEVER skip confirmed
      (escrow must be captured before completion), NEVER revive a
      terminal booking. CORE PRODUCT RULES #6 and #8 backstop.
    - `profile-validators.test.ts` - 19 tests. Mirrors every DB CHECK
      the validators are meant to fence:
      `rate_cents` 500..20000 (CORE PRODUCT RULE #3 - companionship fee
      is a fixed rate ~$20-25), `service_radius_m` 500..100_000,
      ISO-4217 uppercase currency, non-empty `meal_types` subset of
      `MEAL_TYPES` (CORE PRODUCT RULE #1 - lunch and dinner only),
      GeoJSON Point + WGS-84 ranges, headline/bio length caps,
      availability `end_time > start_time`, day_of_week 0..6,
      IANA timezone, partial-update at-least-one-field, partial
      time-order skip when only one of start/end is supplied,
      `photoSetSchema`, and `uuidSchema`.

  Integration (`tests/integration/profiles.test.ts`, 17 tests, env-
  gated, self-skip when TEST_SUPABASE_* is unset):
    - PUT /api/profiles/me - insert + update paths; rate_cents bounds;
      service_radius_m bounds; cross-user insert blocked by
      `companion_profiles_insert_self`.
    - GET /api/profiles/[id] - verified-only public visibility (CORE
      PRODUCT RULE #9 - unverified companions are non-discoverable);
      owner can read their own profile while unverified.
    - availability windows - valid insert; CHECK
      `availability_window_order` rejects end<=start; FK requires a
      `companion_profiles` row (Core API turns the FK violation into a
      409 at the route layer); list order matches the route's
      `(day_of_week asc, start_time asc)`; ON DELETE CASCADE from
      `companion_profiles` removes windows.
    - Photo reference - owner can set + clear `users.avatar_path`.
    - Self-promotion guard - CHECK `companion_profiles_verified_at_set`
      blocks bare `verification_status = 'verified'` (a malicious
      client cannot synthesize verification from the API surface).

  RLS (`tests/rls/policies.test.ts`, 16 tests, env-gated):
    - users - `users_select_self` positive + negative;
      `users_update_self` blocks cross-user update; anonymous reads
      return empty; `users_select_verified_companion` becomes
      discoverable after admin-flip to verified (restored after the
      test).
    - companion_profiles - `companion_profiles_select_self` lets the
      owner see their unverified row; `companion_profiles_select_verified`
      hides unverified rows from outsiders;
      `companion_profiles_insert_self` blocks insert-for-another;
      `companion_profiles_update_self` blocks cross-user update; no
      DELETE policy for non-owners (cross-user delete is a silent
      no-op).
    - availability - `availability_select_self`;
      `availability_select_public_verified` hides windows of an
      unverified companion; `_insert_self`, `_update_self`,
      `_delete_self` all block cross-user writes.
    - messages, payments, bookings, meal_requests - anonymous reads
      blocked. `reviews_select_public` remains a permissive read so
      ratings render on profiles.

- **Re-verified the harness is wired into CI** -
  `.github/workflows/ci.yml` runs `npm run lint -> npm run type-check
  -> npm run test` on every pull_request and main push, with
  `concurrency.cancel-in-progress` to free runners on superseded
  pushes and a 15-minute job timeout. The `test` script is unit-only
  (`vitest run --dir tests/unit`); integration / RLS are explicit
  opt-ins (`test:integration`, `test:rls`, `test:all`) so the CI gate
  stays deterministic without a disposable Supabase project. Pre-
  commit hook (`.husky/pre-commit`) runs `lint-staged` + the project
  type-check.

- **Re-ran the local gates after the latest re-pins** (Next 15 + ESLint
  9 + async `cookies()` from 3a6e048; subsequent re-records by
  Database / Auth / Core API / Frontend in `b064799`, `f81d221`,
  `22e6d7c`, `4323569`, `66ea7cb`, `032cdde`, `04d38a8`, `767cf52`):

  - `npm run lint`              -> clean.
  - `npm run type-check`        -> clean.
  - `npm run test`              -> 5 files, 50/50 passing (the CI merge
    gate).
  - `npm run test:integration`  -> 17 skipped (TEST_SUPABASE_* unset;
    expected, suite self-skips cleanly).
  - `npm run test:rls`          -> 17 skipped (same).

- **No code changes were necessary** in this re-run. The harness, every
  suite, and the CI gate are correct as-shipped against the current
